postcontent: Interested buyers email me directly via dureign21@reborn.com I have been asked by a few as to why this gun has a 16" barrel and not a 20" barrel. Based on internet research and blogs Kengs dealt directly with the Chinese and ordered AK's. Most National Match receivers do indeed have a 20" barrel. They were not popular and did not sell well. Shortly before the ban Kengs ordered a few National Match rifles with the shorter more desirable 16" barrel. The Chinese were happy to build pretty much whatever an importer desired. This Poly Technologies National Match 16" variant is quiet rare as very few were brought in before the Ban. I have found only a couple of other examples pictured on the internet. If I end up finishing it, it will be the original Bright Lime color with white vinyl top and I planned to add white Mach1 stripes and white Sprint hood stripes (I have the new vinyl top and all of the stripes already)  All of the windows, windshields, glass is out of the car, along with most of the interior. I have everything except for a new windshield. I started buying new interior components and still have all of the original except for the carpet.  I have many boxes of new and old parts, piles of receipts, a good bit of literature/shop manuals I have an Elite Marti report (16x20 framed) that displays a copy of the original window sticker/price sheet, VIN door decal, and a statistical breakdown of options and rarity. This took 6 months to process and cost $250 I have color copies of the original 1972 Maryland title (it is currently a PA title in my name)(I am the second owner) The car sat for many (20+) years before I got it with 53,000 original miles on it. Before I brought it in for the full restoration, I did the mechanical and suspension parts and enjoyed driving it for over 8000 miles.  Aside from there being no windshield in the car, it is completely drive-able. It starts right up, sounds great, and every light is hooked up and working.  I would love to finish it and keep it, but unfortunately I could use the money more right now.  Not counting my own seemingly endless amount of hours of labor, I am just looking to get back the money I put out in parts and labor to other people.  Please - only serious buyers and inquiries $17,500 is the asking price That is less than what I have into it at this point. Don't expect me to come down much in price. I would rather keep it. I'm already taking a loss at this price. I am not desperate to sell it, so PLEASE - NO ridiculous, lowball offers or any negative/rude commentsI may consider a partial trade for firearm(s), but with mostly cash to go with it.Trade interests would be: Colt Pythons, Diamodback, Nice S&W revolvers (357mag, 38spcl and 22lr), Minty older Remington rifles (308win and 22lr mainly), and Wingmaster's (12gauge), Maybe a nice Norinco Hunter or CZ527 in 7.62x39  This can be completed as a very nice restoration to drive or show and well worth the investment.I can deliver the truckload of parts if need be within a reasonable distance.
